        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:40PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 340 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles east of Alva, or 20 miles north of Sundance, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colony, Alva, and Bear Lodge Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
